# LifeOS — Architecture

## Tech Stack (decided — do not deviate without strong reason)

### Frontend
- **React Native + Expo SDK 52** — cross-platform Android + iOS from one codebase
- **Expo Router** — file-based navigation (like Next.js but for mobile)
- **TypeScript strict mode** — no `any` types, ever
- **NativeWind** — Tailwind CSS utility classes for React Native
- **expo-av** — voice recording
- **expo-notifications** — push notifications (FCM on Android)
- **expo-sqlite** — local offline storage (offline-first architecture)

### AI
- **Claude Haiku** → classification, entity extraction, morning briefing (cheap, fast)
- **Claude Sonnet** → AI chat, prioritization, cross-entry reasoning (on-demand only)
- **Whisper API (OpenAI)** → voice audio → text transcription
- **Supabase Edge Functions** → server-side AI orchestration (keeps API keys off device)

### Backend
- **Supabase** (NOT AWS — too much DevOps overhead for this scale)
  - Postgres — primary relational database
  - Row Level Security — all data scoped to single user
  - Edge Functions (Deno runtime) — AI calls, scheduled jobs
  - pg_cron — morning briefing at 7am, anti-entropy weekly, spaced rep updates
  - Realtime — for cross-device sync

### Dev Tooling
- **Cursor** — primary IDE for writing code
- **Claude Code** — terminal agent for scaffolding, migrations, debugging
- **Expo Go** — test on real device during development (no build needed)
- **EAS Build** — generate APK/IPA when ready to ship
- **GitHub** — version control, never commit .env

